definitions.definition: Consisting of or containing more than one of something.
examples: The notion of culture is one whose meanings are plural and shifting.

definitions.definition: In systems of number, not singular or not singular or dual.
examples: English nouns usually have singular and plural forms.

definitions.definition: Having some form of multiplicity , especially dissociative identity disorder .
